Tenth Generation

22124. Glen D. Bunch was born on 4 January 1935 in Jamestown, Russell Co., KY. Glen died in Jamestown, Russell Co., KY on 1 January 1998 and was buried at Phelps Cemetery in Jamestown, Russell Co., KY on 3 January 1998 .48375

Glen D. Bunch, 62, of Jamestown, died Thursday, Jan. 1, 1998, at his residence.

He was born in Jamestown on Jan. 4, 1935 to Dorothy Appleby Bunch who survives in Jamestown and Theodore Bunch who preceded him in death.

Mr. Bunch is also survived by his wife - Ruth Johnson Bunch; three sons - Michael Bunch, Larry Bunch and Billy Bunch; five daughters - Linda B. Hawkins, Brenda Bunch, Brenda J. Bunch, Mary R. Conner and Perry Bunch, all of Jamestown. Nice grandchildren also survive.

Others survivors include tow brothers, Arvin Bunch of London and Lle Bunch of Jamestown; three sisters - Rena Buchanan of Indianapolis, Ind., Mary Young and Joyce Coe, both of Jamestown.

He was a farmer.

Funeral services were Sunday, Jan. 4, at 2 p.m. at H. E. Pruitt Memory Chapels Inc. with Bro. Robert Conner officiating. Special music provided by Diana Hughes and Bobby Dunbar.

Active pallbearers were James Johnson, Jerry Johnson, Randall Brumley, James Hawkins, Gene Dunn and Doug Anderson.

Honorary pallbearers were Joshua Bunch and Jimmy Keen.

Interment was in Phelps Cemetery in Jamestown.
